  voxrt_wake_word.vxrt

The model weights are proprietary, trained in-house by Elephant
Enterprises LLC on 100% synthetic data. No upstream model
checkpoints, no copyleft or attribution obligations on the weights
themselves.

1. PERMITTED USES

   You may use, link against, and redistribute this `.vxrt` file
   as an unmodified part of the official `voxrt-wake-word-android`
   or `voxrt-wake-word-ios` libraries at the version it was
   resolved with.

   Redistribution as part of your own consumer applications —
   including commercial App Store / Play Store apps — is permitted
   without per-installation fees, royalties, or registration, for
   the on-device wake-phrase detection task the file is built for.

   You may run the model on production user devices.

2. RESTRICTIONS

   You may not:

   (a) Modify, repackage, or relink the `.vxrt` outside the
       unmodified official VoxRT consumer libraries.

   (b) Reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise
       attempt to derive the underlying weight tensors, the model
       topology beyond what is publicly described in the VoxRT
       documentation, or any other internal state of the file.

   (c) Bypass, defeat, or remove the AES-256-GCM encryption that
       protects the weights at rest (per ADR-0023), nor distribute
       a decrypted copy of the weights.

   (d) Train derivative wake-word models from outputs produced
       by this model on real user audio, or build distillation /
       knowledge-extraction pipelines that depend on this model
       producing soft targets.

3. WAKE-PHRASE SCOPE

   The default model detects the phrase "Hey Assistant" only.
   Custom phrases (your own brand name, multi-phrase detection,
   language extension) are part of the commercial VoxRT SDK tier.
   Contact help@voxrt.com for custom-phrase model training.

